UNITED STATES of America v. Beulah COX, Administratrix. No. 1370. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Jan. 28, 1935. Randolph C. Shaw, Sp. Asst, to Atty. Gen., for the United States. William A. Tidwell, of Idabel, Old., for appellee.

Before PPIILLIPS, McDERMOTT, and BRATTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed pursuant to agreement of counsel.
